trend_summary: Built-up footprint grows gradually, concentrating north and along the west highway corridor. Industrial estates spread south-west, while new housing clusters fill southern townships. Farmland parcels rearrange; some fields convert to woodland, others to construction. Transport links are upgraded, adding junctions and widening the main artery. Overall, moderate growth keeps the landscape predominantly suburban with medium density.
notable_changes: Industrial/warehouse complexes expand along the western highway corridor after the second image.
New residential subdivisions appear south-east of the main town from the third frame onward.
Central highway gains an additional interchange and lane widening, improving connectivity.
Several farmland blocks transition to forest or green space, especially in the north-east.
Extensive earthworks or flood-control alterations emerge along the western riverbanks in the latest image.
